From b6cdbb66c94bfaabfcb99c4e5c4aa3a2d3de8f51 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ESTI Contributors <esti@example.local>
Date: Sat, 13 Jun 2026 07:22:55 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 3/5] Dashboard: health edge per card, monochrome outline tags
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Carbon notification anatomy applied to dashboard cards: a 3px left border is
now each card's single colour signal (support tokens only — error = needs
attention, warning = watch, success = healthy, border-subtle = neutral/info).
With urgency on the edge, tags drop their fill colours and switch to
Tag type="outline" — text carries the meaning.

- edge(health) helper + CardHealth type; applied to every KPI chip, Action
  Center, financial tiles, project health board, client signals, team cards,
  revision/technical quality tiles, filing tiles, and activity feed
- Edge derivation: KPI chips from their own metric; Action Center from open
  count; project board and client table from worst row; team cards from
  capacity; revisions from risk band; technical from accuracy/query thresholds;
  filing tiles from the most urgent due date
- All tags converted to outline except per-row Health/Risk tags inside the
  project and client tables, which keep fills (rows have no edge of their own)
- Scope drift and drawing-accuracy values render as plain bold text instead of
  coloured tags; removed now-unused CAPACITY_TAG / PERFORMANCE_BAND_TAG /
  dueTagType helpers

Co-Authored-By: Codex Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
